-- More Than 10% of Johannesburg Police Probed for Offenses, The Star Reports
-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 2010-11-03T06:54:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/more-than-10-of-johannesburg-police-probed-for-offenses-the-star-reports.html
More than 10 percent of police
officers in Johannesburg have been investigated in the past year
for bribery, theft, assault and other offenses, The  Star 
reported, citing the police department’s annual report.  Of the 476 metro police officers who were probed, 19 were
dismissed, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said. The city’s
police department currently employs 4,326 staff, The Star said.  South African President  Jacob Zuma  has pledged to cut the
levels of crime and corruption in the country. The country’s
murder rate is 34.1 per 100,000, according to police data.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Nasreen Seria in Johannesburg at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg at 
